    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_CustomDialog_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>You can create a new dialog from scratch. You can configure its content, the displayed buttons, their text, and whether they are enabled or not. Below you will find only a few customization options — all other parameters are configured programmatically.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Prefabs_Header" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Ready dialog prefabs</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Prefabs_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>You can also use ready-made dialog prefabs that are suitable for most tasks, such as text input, selecting a geolocation point, choosing a file, and so on. Some parameters in them, such as the message or button availability, can also be customized. Prefabs are divided into two types: custom dialogs created manually for specific tasks, and system dialogs such as the file picker.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_System_SelectFolder_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to select a folder. Returns the path to the chosen folder. The dialog title and initial location can be customized.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_System_SaveFile_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to save a file. Returns the file path. You can set the title, default extension, type filter, and initial directory.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_System_OpenFile_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to open a file. Returns the file path. You can set the title, type filter, and initial directory.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_System_ObserveFolder_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Shows the contents of the selected folder. Does not return anything. The dialog title and default path can be specified.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Custom_YesOrNo_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to agree or decline. Returns true or false. The dialog title and message can be customized.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Custom_HotKeyCapture_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to choose a hotkey by pressing it. Returns information about the selected hotkey. The title, message, and current hotkey can be specified.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Custom_GeoPoint_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to select a point on the map. Returns GeoPoint. The initial location can be set.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Custom_Input_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Allows the user to enter text. Returns the entered value. The dialog title and message can be customized.</value>
    </data>
    <data name="DialogControlsPageView_Custom_Save_Description" xml:space="preserve">
        <value>Used to confirm saving information. Returns true or false. The dialog title and message can be specified.</value>
    </data>
